body_html:
Python 2 and python 3 have quite a bit of differences. Here is a small number of them:
https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/important-differences-between-python-2-x-and-python-3-x-with-examples/

So it can really be as simple as division operator behaving differently, or maybe the two different python distros rounding numbers differently, or random number generators behaving differently. There are a lot of possibilities.
